// Terminal size (designs/techdesign-terminal-floor.md §2). On a pty the driver
// sets a known window size and expects it back; on a pipe/non-tty sysWinSize
// fails and term::size() falls back to the 24x80 default (raw mode is off, so
// the cursor-report probe is skipped). Same source, every engine.
term::WinSize s = term::size();
console.writeln(s.rows.toString() + "x" + s.cols.toString());
